The paper deals with lower bounds and polynomial identity testing for a model of algebraic branching programs, which are typically studied in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The subexponential-time PIT algorithm also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of circuit complexity techniques, which could potentially place it in the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR).
